WEBVTT

00:00.420 --> 00:02.830
♪♪

00:04.290 --> 00:05.380
Andi:
Previously on Andi Mack...

00:05.380 --> 00:06.750
Choco Chocolate
Chip Muffin, right?

00:06.750 --> 00:08.460
Scary Basketball Guy.

00:08.460 --> 00:09.750
Actually, TJ.

00:09.750 --> 00:11.380
Buffy may have
been right, but...

00:11.380 --> 00:13.380
you're the one who
really helped me.

00:13.380 --> 00:15.420
Cyrus:
He's a completely
different person.

00:15.420 --> 00:17.170
He's with me.

00:17.170 --> 00:19.330
I'm the new principal,
Dr. Metcalf.

00:19.330 --> 00:21.460
I want you know,
I'm not a scary principal.

00:21.460 --> 00:23.040
I'm an approachable one.
I don't see any reason

00:23.040 --> 00:23.960
why we can't be friends.

00:23.960 --> 00:25.460
Our lease...

00:25.460 --> 00:26.290
was accepted.

00:26.290 --> 00:27.580
Are you
two moving?

00:27.580 --> 00:29.420
We're gonna need a bigger place
when we get married.

00:29.420 --> 00:30.830
The apartment next door!

00:30.830 --> 00:31.920
-(smash)
-(Andi screaming)

00:31.920 --> 00:33.290
Surprise!

00:33.290 --> 00:34.620
I'm gonna knock this wall out,
and before you know it,

00:34.620 --> 00:35.920
we'll have one
big apartment!

00:36.670 --> 00:38.580
♪ ♪

00:38.960 --> 00:40.460
Andi:
Next question!

00:40.460 --> 00:41.670
What is the name

00:41.670 --> 00:43.460
of my favorite stuffed animal?

00:43.460 --> 00:44.460
Eh! Baba!

00:44.460 --> 00:46.290
-Correct!
-Yes.

00:46.290 --> 00:47.250
Andi:
Next question.

00:47.250 --> 00:48.460
What is my favorite condiment?

00:48.460 --> 00:49.500
Eh!

00:49.500 --> 00:50.540
That's a trick question.

00:50.540 --> 00:51.580
You don't like condiments.

00:51.580 --> 00:53.330
Correct! (sighs)

00:53.330 --> 00:55.120
The score is Bex five,

00:55.120 --> 00:56.380
Bowie zero.

00:56.380 --> 00:58.830
Having a little trouble
with your buzzer, sport?

00:58.830 --> 01:00.500
This isn't fair.

01:00.500 --> 01:02.000
You guys have spent
way more time together.

01:02.000 --> 01:03.380
And whose fault is that?

01:03.380 --> 01:04.540
Yours.

01:04.540 --> 01:05.620
For not telling me she existed

01:05.620 --> 01:07.380
for the first
13 years of her life.

01:07.380 --> 01:08.460
Next question!

01:09.330 --> 01:10.620
What is...

01:10.620 --> 01:12.330
my favorite eating utensil?

01:12.330 --> 01:14.120
Bzzz! Your hands.

01:14.120 --> 01:16.250
That's your favorite
eating utensil.

01:16.250 --> 01:18.120
I thought it was everyone's
favorite eating utensil.

01:18.120 --> 01:19.460
-(chuckles)
-(knocking)

01:19.460 --> 01:20.920
I'll go see who it is.
Don't get up.

01:20.920 --> 01:23.250
(groans)
I wasn't going to.

01:27.080 --> 01:28.420
(gasps) Mom!

01:28.420 --> 01:31.000
Steven! Ohh!

01:31.000 --> 01:32.210
♪ ♪

01:35.000 --> 01:36.420
(chuckles)

01:36.420 --> 01:37.790
Steven?

01:37.790 --> 01:40.080
(theme song playing)

01:40.080 --> 01:43.540
♪ I'm standin'
on the edge ♪

01:43.540 --> 01:48.040
♪ And everything I know-oh-oh
is blown away ♪

01:49.540 --> 01:52.880
♪ Life is upside down ♪

01:52.880 --> 01:57.420
♪ But any way it goes
I'll work it out ♪

01:59.120 --> 02:02.540
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh ♪

02:02.540 --> 02:06.290
♪ Here we go ♪

02:06.290 --> 02:09.500
-♪ One, two, three ♪
-♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

02:09.500 --> 02:11.830
♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪

02:11.830 --> 02:14.170
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

02:14.170 --> 02:16.500
♪ But I'm with you
all the way ♪

02:16.500 --> 02:18.880
♪ I'm ready for tomorrow ♪

02:18.880 --> 02:21.380
-♪ Tomorrow starts today ♪
-♪ Hey ♪

02:21.380 --> 02:23.500
♪ There ain't a map to follow ♪

02:23.500 --> 02:25.620
♪ But I'm with you
all the way ♪

02:25.620 --> 02:26.670
♪ Hey ♪

02:26.670 --> 02:28.460
♪ All the way ♪

02:28.920 --> 02:31.120
Oh! (chuckles)

02:31.120 --> 02:33.040
Steven's his
actual first name.

02:34.080 --> 02:35.250
Whoa.

02:35.830 --> 02:36.880
Rebecca?

02:36.880 --> 02:37.710
Cookie!

02:37.710 --> 02:39.580
-It's been too long!
-Oh!

02:40.460 --> 02:41.830
Steven and Rebecca...

02:41.830 --> 02:42.670
Okay!
(chuckles)

02:43.880 --> 02:45.670
Is this my granddaughter?

02:45.670 --> 02:47.710
Look at you.
You're so beautiful!

02:47.710 --> 02:48.540
I'm Cookie.

02:48.540 --> 02:49.790
I'm Andi.

02:49.790 --> 02:52.620
But, that's not short
for anything. It's just Andi.

02:52.620 --> 02:53.500
I love you already!

02:53.500 --> 02:55.380
(both laughing)

02:55.380 --> 02:56.540
You're really good at hugging.

02:56.540 --> 02:58.170
Mom, you should've told
us you were coming.

02:58.170 --> 02:59.460
I didn't know
until yesterday.

02:59.460 --> 03:01.080
-Oh, just a little more.
Just a little more.
-Oh!

03:01.080 --> 03:02.920
You're just so precious!

03:02.920 --> 03:04.500
(sighs) Okay, I'm good.
(chuckles)

03:04.500 --> 03:07.620
So, I've heard so many
stories about you.

03:07.620 --> 03:10.040
Is it true you live
on cruise ships?

03:10.040 --> 03:12.580
It's like living in an apartment
without traffic noise,

03:12.580 --> 03:14.790
and all the neighbors
serve you drinks...

03:14.790 --> 03:16.000
in a coconut!

03:16.000 --> 03:17.580
Mom has been all
over the world.

03:17.580 --> 03:21.250
But, I told myself when I got
back to this hemisphere,

03:21.250 --> 03:23.000
I was going to
come straight here,

03:23.000 --> 03:24.250
and meet my granddaughter.

03:25.170 --> 03:26.250
Mom, do you want
something to drink?

03:26.250 --> 03:27.120
Do you have a coconut?

03:27.960 --> 03:29.540
Just kidding.
I brought my own.

03:30.540 --> 03:32.460
Are you hungry?
We were just having dinner.

03:32.460 --> 03:35.250
Cookie:
Is this what you're
feeding my granddaughter?

03:35.250 --> 03:36.080
This won't do.

03:36.080 --> 03:37.540
Let me fix you kids something.

03:37.540 --> 03:39.080
Mom, you don't
have to do that.

03:39.080 --> 03:40.540
No, no,
it's no trouble.

03:40.540 --> 03:42.580
Well, it might be. There's
not a lot in there.

03:42.580 --> 03:44.000
I'll be fine.

03:44.000 --> 03:45.580
I'll holler when dinner's ready.

03:45.580 --> 03:47.750
♪ ♪

03:47.750 --> 03:48.920
(laughs)

03:48.920 --> 03:51.250
Well, Steven.

03:51.250 --> 03:52.580
(laughs)

03:55.920 --> 03:57.120
Dinner!

03:57.120 --> 03:59.710
It's only been,
like, 20 minutes!

03:59.710 --> 04:01.880
She's just showing off.
Trying to impress you guys.

04:08.250 --> 04:09.790
(laughs)

04:09.790 --> 04:11.580
It's working.

04:11.580 --> 04:13.580
♪ ♪

04:16.500 --> 04:18.170
How did the...

04:18.170 --> 04:19.420
Where did the...

04:19.420 --> 04:22.210
Does your bag have
a frozen food section?

04:22.210 --> 04:24.500
I never go anywhere
without a roast chicken.

04:24.500 --> 04:26.670
Cookie:
The drumstick is
Steven's favorite.

04:26.670 --> 04:28.880
He loves to eat
with his hands.

04:28.880 --> 04:30.710
♪ ♪

04:30.710 --> 04:31.830
(giggles)

04:36.210 --> 04:37.880
-TJ: Cyrus!
-Hey! What's up?

04:37.880 --> 04:39.790
What are you
doing Saturday?

04:39.790 --> 04:41.750
Saturday. Saturday...

04:41.750 --> 04:45.420
Well, my Popular Kids Club
meeting's are on Fridays,

04:45.420 --> 04:46.960
so, uh, yeah.
I'm free on Saturday.

04:46.960 --> 04:48.880
-Wanna hang out?
-With you?

04:48.880 --> 04:50.170
And my friends.

04:50.170 --> 04:51.580
Do they even know I exist?

04:51.580 --> 04:53.170
Yeah, they know.

04:53.170 --> 04:54.000
I talk about you.

04:54.000 --> 04:55.120
Behind my back?

04:55.120 --> 04:57.420
Well, you're not there,
so, yeah.

04:58.210 --> 04:59.210
Are you mad?

04:59.210 --> 05:00.960
Are you kidding?

05:00.960 --> 05:02.250
I'm flattered!

05:02.250 --> 05:04.170
I didn't think anybody
talked about me behind my back.

05:04.170 --> 05:06.170
So, Saturday. You in?

05:06.170 --> 05:07.500
What's the plan?

05:07.500 --> 05:09.000
Nothing major.
Just gonna hang out.

05:09.000 --> 05:12.080
Cool, cool. Definitely
down for some hanging.

05:12.080 --> 05:14.250
Or up for some hanging.

05:14.250 --> 05:16.420
Direction doesn't matter.
I can hang. Yeah.

05:16.420 --> 05:17.880
-Okay. See ya.
-Yeah.

05:23.710 --> 05:26.710
Mom. People are talking
about me behind my back!

05:27.790 --> 05:29.830
I know. I'm proud of me, too.

05:29.830 --> 05:30.670
(laughs)

05:31.580 --> 05:33.170
Buffy:
Hey!

05:33.170 --> 05:34.710
-Oh, I like your board!
-You want it?

05:35.500 --> 05:37.040
-What?
-Seriously, take it.

05:37.040 --> 05:39.460
(laughs)
If you insist...

05:40.460 --> 05:42.380
-I really like your jacket--
-I'm keeping my jacket.

05:42.380 --> 05:43.710
Had to try.
(laughs)

05:43.710 --> 05:46.080
Now I have an excuse
to get a new board.

05:46.080 --> 05:47.710
-I mean, this thing
is pretty beat.
-(chuckles)

05:47.710 --> 05:49.120
You might wanna
replace the wheels.

05:49.120 --> 05:51.080
I'll go to
the skate shop
this weekend.

05:51.080 --> 05:53.460
I'll go with you! You can
help me pick out a new deck.

05:53.460 --> 05:55.500
And then you can teach
me some new tricks.

05:55.500 --> 05:57.620
And before we know it,
I'll be better than you.

05:57.620 --> 05:59.500
And then I'll wake you up
because you'll be dreaming.

05:59.500 --> 06:01.290
And then I'll wake you up
because you were dreaming

06:01.290 --> 06:02.790
about waking me up.

06:02.790 --> 06:04.170
-And then I'll...
-Hmm?

06:04.170 --> 06:05.790
-Yeah, that's enough.
-I'll take that.

06:07.710 --> 06:10.920
No skateboarding inside school
or on school grounds.

06:10.920 --> 06:12.250
Dr. Metcalf,
we weren't skating.

06:12.250 --> 06:13.460
I was just
holding it.

06:13.460 --> 06:14.790
Holding is
a gateway to riding.

06:14.790 --> 06:16.580
You can pick it up
after school.

06:16.580 --> 06:18.000
Are those leggings?

06:18.000 --> 06:19.960
Oh right, we changed
the dress code, didn't we?

06:19.960 --> 06:21.210
Carry on.

06:21.210 --> 06:22.710
♪ ♪

06:22.710 --> 06:24.670
What is his problem?

06:24.670 --> 06:27.790
Not his hearing.
Ears working just fine.

06:33.830 --> 06:36.710
Bex:
She rearranged
all the furniture?

06:36.710 --> 06:38.580
Mom?

06:40.290 --> 06:41.880
What do you think?

06:41.880 --> 06:43.330
I'm so happy to be here.

06:43.330 --> 06:45.460
I'm just looking for little
ways to make you happy.

06:45.460 --> 06:47.120
I hope you love it!

06:47.120 --> 06:48.580
Be honest, do you love it?

06:48.580 --> 06:51.460
♪ ♪

06:53.380 --> 06:54.580
What's not to love?

06:55.120 --> 06:56.790
-(timer rings)
-Oh, that's my cue!

06:56.790 --> 06:58.120
Make yourselves at home!

07:07.420 --> 07:09.250
What did she do?

07:10.000 --> 07:11.920
How did she...

07:11.920 --> 07:13.710
Why did she...

07:13.710 --> 07:15.790
When did she...

07:15.790 --> 07:18.040
You gotta admit,
it's an improvement. Huh.

07:18.880 --> 07:20.250
Hole.

07:20.250 --> 07:21.620
No hole.

07:21.620 --> 07:22.830
Hole.

07:22.830 --> 07:24.080
(chuckles)
No hole.

07:24.080 --> 07:25.920
I liked everything
the way it was.

07:27.790 --> 07:29.750
-Hole.
-Stop playing with that!

07:29.750 --> 07:31.170
(sighs)
It's our house,

07:31.170 --> 07:32.790
and it's our furniture.

07:32.790 --> 07:34.960
She said we should be honest.
I'm just gonna tell her.

07:34.960 --> 07:36.830
(sniffs)
Oh, I smell cookies.

07:36.830 --> 07:38.920
Cookie:
Look what I found
in the oven!

07:38.920 --> 07:40.500
Your favorite!

07:40.500 --> 07:42.500
Everything she makes
is your favorite.

07:42.500 --> 07:43.830
(giggles)

07:43.830 --> 07:44.960
Name cookies?

07:44.960 --> 07:46.170
(gasps) Oh!

07:46.170 --> 07:47.790
Those are my favorite!

07:47.790 --> 07:48.620
Tell you what.

07:48.620 --> 07:50.500
After you've had your snack,

07:50.500 --> 07:51.920
I'll wrap you each in a lovey,

07:51.920 --> 07:54.290
and find you something
nice to watch on TV!

07:54.290 --> 07:55.920
Mom, you're the best.

07:55.920 --> 07:57.330
No, you're the best!

07:57.330 --> 07:58.920
No, you're the best!

07:58.920 --> 08:01.250
♪ ♪

08:01.250 --> 08:03.250
I hate to even take
a bite out of it.

08:06.000 --> 08:07.500
Your cookie's much
bigger than mine.

08:07.500 --> 08:10.000
That's why I let her
call me "Rebecca."

08:10.000 --> 08:12.080
-No fair.
-Mm-hmm.

08:14.420 --> 08:16.080
(dirt bikes revving)

08:16.080 --> 08:19.080
(heavy metal music)

08:26.830 --> 08:28.920
(heavy metal singing)

08:28.920 --> 08:31.000
♪ Never let him get away ♪

08:31.000 --> 08:33.210
♪ Oh no, here I come ♪

08:33.210 --> 08:34.830
♪ Running into the rain ♪

08:34.830 --> 08:38.500
♪ I'm gonna run ♪

08:38.500 --> 08:41.960
♪ Right until the end ♪

08:42.880 --> 08:46.790
♪ I'm gonna run ♪

08:46.790 --> 08:47.880
(scrapes dirt)

08:48.290 --> 08:49.120
Hey.

08:54.210 --> 08:56.210
-(music ends)
-Hey, you made it!

08:56.210 --> 08:58.830
Uh, Cyrus, this is Lester,
and this is Reed.

08:58.830 --> 09:00.000
Hey.

09:00.000 --> 09:01.460
You didn't tell me there
were gonna be dirt bikes.

09:01.460 --> 09:02.420
Ever been on one?

09:02.420 --> 09:04.380
As a matter of fact,
Andi has one,

09:04.380 --> 09:05.790
and I hid it in my garage,

09:05.790 --> 09:08.000
and rolled it through
the school parking lot.

09:08.000 --> 09:09.080
So, no.

09:09.080 --> 09:10.170
They're really fun.

09:10.170 --> 09:11.540
Give it a shot!

09:11.540 --> 09:13.000
No, thanks.

09:13.000 --> 09:14.960
I have a fear of basically
everything that's going on here.

09:14.960 --> 09:16.710
(laughs)
TJ was right.

09:16.710 --> 09:17.830
You are funny.

09:17.830 --> 09:18.750
I don't know.

09:18.750 --> 09:20.040
Well, come on.
Say something else funny.

09:20.040 --> 09:22.830
My humor's mostly observational
and character driven.

09:22.830 --> 09:24.500
(laughs)

09:24.500 --> 09:25.790
That's good, that's good.

09:25.790 --> 09:26.790
Hot crowd.

09:26.790 --> 09:27.790
You gonna ride?

09:27.790 --> 09:28.880
Ah, I'm good.

09:28.880 --> 09:30.790
What is it,
you don't got a bike?

09:30.790 --> 09:32.000
Use mine, man.

09:32.000 --> 09:34.960
That's okay. I have
a complicated relationship
with wheels.

09:34.960 --> 09:37.000
Okay. I get it.

09:37.000 --> 09:38.420
It's not really
your thing.

09:39.330 --> 09:41.120
Well, maybe it
could be your thing.

09:41.120 --> 09:43.380
You'll never really
know unless you try.

09:43.380 --> 09:45.460
♪ ♪

09:46.920 --> 09:48.210
-So, this is clutch.
-Clutch.

09:48.210 --> 09:50.920
Push in the, uh,
shifter, right?

09:50.920 --> 09:52.750
You keep
the clutch in.

09:52.750 --> 09:55.040
One down, four up.
Okay?

09:55.040 --> 09:57.250
Try it. Switch gears. Okay.

09:57.250 --> 09:58.880
Brake right there.
Give it a little demo.

09:58.880 --> 10:00.750
Okay? You gotta be
pretty firm with that.

10:00.750 --> 10:02.960
Cyrus:
All right. That's why they
call it a kick-start.

10:02.960 --> 10:04.080
Yeah.

10:04.080 --> 10:05.500
Not bad,
not bad.

10:05.500 --> 10:06.790
-All right.
-♪ But you gotta push hard ♪

10:06.790 --> 10:09.250
♪ Till you get to the top ♪

10:09.250 --> 10:10.330
-Okay, grab it?
-Got it?

10:10.330 --> 10:11.380
-Grab it?
-Yeah.

10:12.420 --> 10:13.500
♪ Now you're wishing ♪

10:13.500 --> 10:16.210
♪ It's time to attack,
bring it on ♪

10:16.210 --> 10:17.960
Nice!

10:17.960 --> 10:19.830
♪ Bring it on ♪

10:21.750 --> 10:23.380
-All right, let's go, Cyrus.
-Woo!

10:23.380 --> 10:25.000
-You got this!
-(mouthing)

10:25.000 --> 10:27.540
(dirt bike revving unevenly)

10:27.540 --> 10:29.880
(metal music continues)

10:29.880 --> 10:32.960
(dirt bike revving)

10:32.960 --> 10:34.500
Let's go!

10:34.500 --> 10:35.330
Stop.

10:35.330 --> 10:37.380
(music continues)

10:39.000 --> 10:40.750
♪ Bring it on ♪

10:42.830 --> 10:45.250
Come on, come on. Do it again,
Cyrus. You got this.

10:45.250 --> 10:48.040
(revving, tires screech)

10:51.250 --> 10:53.040
-Come on, dude!
Keep going, keep going.
-Come on, dude. Come on!

10:53.040 --> 10:54.250
-Keep going. One more time.
One more time.
-Come on!

10:54.250 --> 10:55.290
Come on, come on!

10:55.290 --> 10:58.000
(dirt bike revving)

10:59.710 --> 11:00.750
(music continues)

11:00.750 --> 11:03.170
(both cheering)

11:03.170 --> 11:06.000
Woo! Yeah! Let's go!

11:06.000 --> 11:07.080
Yeah!

11:07.080 --> 11:08.710
-TJ: Nice!
-Woo!

11:08.710 --> 11:09.920
Nice, dude.

11:09.920 --> 11:11.710
Look at you! I think you got
a little air on that one.

11:11.710 --> 11:13.120
I forgot which
one was the brake.

11:13.120 --> 11:14.380
You lost your shoe, dude.

11:16.710 --> 11:18.210
Huh. That's so on brand for me.

11:18.210 --> 11:19.710
Yo, check it out.

11:19.710 --> 11:20.830
I got a great shot of you.

11:20.830 --> 11:22.620
I look rugged!

11:22.620 --> 11:24.210
Oh, and there's my shoe!

11:24.210 --> 11:25.170
♪ ♪

11:25.170 --> 11:26.080
Hm.

11:35.040 --> 11:36.330
What is happening?

11:36.330 --> 11:37.670
What's with the furniture?

11:37.670 --> 11:40.250
And why do you two
look like poop emojis?

11:40.250 --> 11:41.620
They're loveys.

11:41.620 --> 11:43.920
-They're one of
Cookie's specialties.
-Do you want one?

11:43.920 --> 11:45.210
-(TV chatter)
-No, thanks.

11:45.210 --> 11:47.460
I like to have
the use of my limbs.

11:47.460 --> 11:50.040
Oh, oh! Can you change
the channel for us then?

11:50.040 --> 11:52.830
The remote control is
right in front of you.

11:52.830 --> 11:55.330
-(whimpering)
-Aw, but then I have
to leave my lovey.

11:55.330 --> 11:57.080
I'm not ready
to leave my lovey.

11:57.080 --> 11:58.170
Me neither.

11:58.170 --> 12:00.500
You two are really
starting to scare me.

12:00.500 --> 12:01.960
Mommy,
we need help!

12:03.210 --> 12:04.120
Bex:
Mommy!

12:04.120 --> 12:06.080
-He said mommy!
-I did.

12:06.080 --> 12:08.330
Now, there's no reason
to be embarrassed.

12:08.330 --> 12:11.380
No matter how old you get,
I will always be your mommy,

12:11.380 --> 12:12.710
and you will
always be my...

12:12.710 --> 12:15.170
Wittle Stevey-Weevy!

12:15.170 --> 12:16.460
Oh, look who's here!

12:16.460 --> 12:17.500
Baby Num-num!

12:17.500 --> 12:19.250
Baby Num-num?

12:19.250 --> 12:20.710
I am not signing off on that.

12:20.710 --> 12:21.670
Do you want a cookie?

12:21.670 --> 12:23.580
No, thank you.

12:23.580 --> 12:24.710
Let me make you a lovey.

12:24.710 --> 12:27.040
I can't. I have to
be somewhere else.

12:27.040 --> 12:29.210
Oh. (chuckles)

12:29.210 --> 12:31.830
Aw, but then who's gonna
change the channel?

12:31.830 --> 12:34.620
I got you! What do
you kids wanna watch?

12:34.620 --> 12:37.460
Oh, look! There's
a Bob the Taco marathon!

12:37.460 --> 12:39.080
Both:
Bob the Taco!

12:39.080 --> 12:42.670
Bob the Taco! Bob the Taco!

12:42.670 --> 12:44.670
♪ ♪

12:49.960 --> 12:52.210
-I like that one!
-Nice.

12:53.710 --> 12:55.710
You know what you
never say anymore?

12:55.710 --> 12:57.710
Docious magocious.

12:57.710 --> 12:59.710
I feel like I kinda
grew out of it.

12:59.710 --> 13:01.170
That's too bad.

13:02.170 --> 13:03.540
I liked it.

13:05.290 --> 13:06.040
Really?

13:07.210 --> 13:09.080
You always
made fun of it.

13:10.170 --> 13:11.540
That's why I liked it.

13:12.580 --> 13:14.710
-(chuckles)
-(buzzing)

13:14.710 --> 13:15.830
Whoa.

13:16.750 --> 13:18.040
(buzzing continues)

13:19.080 --> 13:21.040
Did you know they
do tattoos here?

13:21.040 --> 13:23.330
It's the same guy who
designs a lot of the decks.

13:23.330 --> 13:24.460
He's really good.

13:24.460 --> 13:25.960
Buffy: Would you
ever get one?

13:25.960 --> 13:28.250
Mmm. I mean,
probably not.

13:28.250 --> 13:30.290
Nothing like that, for sure.

13:30.290 --> 13:32.830
Yeah, you do that if
you're in a punk band.

13:32.830 --> 13:34.330
Or a motorcycle gang.

13:34.330 --> 13:35.580
(whispers)
Or prison.

13:35.580 --> 13:38.580
♪ ♪

13:58.040 --> 13:59.330
♪ ♪

13:59.330 --> 14:01.580
Don't get me wrong.
I love Cookie.

14:01.580 --> 14:03.710
I mean, she's like
the ultimate grandma.

14:03.710 --> 14:04.620
No offense.

14:04.620 --> 14:06.710
None taken because
I'm not a grandma.

14:06.710 --> 14:09.040
Right. Right.

14:09.040 --> 14:10.790
Anyways, I love
everything she does.

14:10.790 --> 14:12.170
You know, the chicken,

14:12.170 --> 14:14.790
the cookies, the hugging.
It's all so good.

14:14.790 --> 14:16.580
Except, then I get home,

14:16.580 --> 14:19.040
and nothing is where
it's supposed be.

14:19.040 --> 14:21.750
And I'm going to have to
hire a nanny for my parents.

14:21.750 --> 14:23.580
Maybe I should get into it.

14:23.580 --> 14:25.250
Grand to Grand combat.

14:25.250 --> 14:26.830
You're not taking
this seriously.

14:26.830 --> 14:29.290
It's like she has them
under some kind of spell.

14:29.290 --> 14:31.000
You know what?

14:31.000 --> 14:32.830
Lemme see for myself.

14:32.830 --> 14:34.250
I should go over there anyway.

14:34.250 --> 14:36.540
I've never met the woman,
and she's gonna be family.

14:36.540 --> 14:38.250
Okay.

14:38.250 --> 14:40.040
But, be careful.

14:40.040 --> 14:41.540
I can't lose anyone else.

14:41.540 --> 14:43.250
Okay.

14:43.250 --> 14:44.460
♪ ♪

14:46.210 --> 14:47.210
(sighs)

14:52.880 --> 14:54.170
-Hey.
-Hey.

14:54.170 --> 14:55.790
-Question about
the watermelons.
-Yeah?

14:55.790 --> 14:57.830
We having some kind of
eating contest or what?

14:57.830 --> 14:59.830
-(laughs) You crack me up, man.
-What'd I say?

14:59.830 --> 15:01.380
-Eating contest?
-Mm-hmm.

15:01.380 --> 15:03.420
We're not gonna eat
the watermelons,
we're gonna shoot them.

15:03.420 --> 15:04.460
-What?
-Yeah.

15:04.460 --> 15:06.330
Dude, have you ever seen
a watermelon go pfft?

15:06.330 --> 15:08.000
It's so dope.

15:08.000 --> 15:10.290
Yeah, sure... super dope.

15:10.290 --> 15:11.330
Did you say shoot them?

15:11.330 --> 15:12.750
-That's right.
-With what?

15:14.120 --> 15:15.500
See for yourself.

15:19.500 --> 15:21.880
(laughs) You should see
your face right now, bro.

15:23.710 --> 15:24.750
Is that real?

15:24.750 --> 15:26.210
Of course it's real.

15:26.210 --> 15:27.290
Where did you get that?

15:27.290 --> 15:28.380
It's my dad's.

15:28.380 --> 15:29.500
Does he know you have it?

15:29.500 --> 15:30.880
Dude, chill.

15:38.250 --> 15:39.330
Wanna hold it?

15:39.330 --> 15:41.290
No.

15:41.290 --> 15:42.920
-No, I definitely do not.
-O-okay, okay.

15:42.920 --> 15:43.920
Okay.

15:49.920 --> 15:51.120
You know what's in that bag?

15:52.380 --> 15:53.170
Yeah.

15:53.830 --> 15:54.880
I'm gonna go.

15:56.380 --> 15:57.210
Okay.

15:57.210 --> 15:58.540
I think you should too.

16:03.540 --> 16:04.920
TJ...

16:09.960 --> 16:11.960
♪ ♪

16:20.420 --> 16:21.790
(quiet TV chatter)

16:27.380 --> 16:28.380
CeCe!

16:29.380 --> 16:30.290
What happened?

16:30.290 --> 16:32.620
She baked me a name cookie.

16:32.620 --> 16:33.960
I never had a chance.

16:33.960 --> 16:35.170
Where is Mom?

16:35.170 --> 16:37.830
She might be napping
in your room.

16:37.830 --> 16:39.330
I wasn't at my most alert.

16:39.330 --> 16:41.460
-And Bowie?
-Kitchen.

16:42.330 --> 16:43.380
(sighs)

16:45.620 --> 16:46.620
♪ ♪

16:46.620 --> 16:47.920
No!

16:49.750 --> 16:50.750
Hands where I can see them!

16:51.710 --> 16:52.540
Drop the scissors!

16:53.460 --> 16:55.710
Nobody touches the hair.

17:10.460 --> 17:12.250
It's just that
I don't get to spend

17:12.250 --> 17:13.330
a lot of time
with Steven.

17:13.330 --> 17:16.250
And so, when we get together,
the mom thing just kicks in.

17:16.250 --> 17:17.670
Boy, does it.

17:18.120 --> 17:20.330
And then, I meet my grandchild
for the first time,

17:20.330 --> 17:21.670
and the grandma thing kicks in.

17:21.670 --> 17:23.580
You put both of
them together,

17:23.580 --> 17:25.330
and watch out,
it's Hurricane Cookie.

17:25.330 --> 17:26.420
(laughs)

17:26.420 --> 17:29.120
Maybe the next time you visit,
you'll be downgraded

17:29.120 --> 17:30.420
to Tropical Storm Cookie.

17:30.420 --> 17:31.960
Oh, I keep forgetting.

17:31.960 --> 17:33.330
I-I have a present for you.

17:33.330 --> 17:35.420
I been carrying
it around all day.

17:35.420 --> 17:38.330
Cookie, you've done
more than enough.

17:38.330 --> 17:41.210
I mean, we're
17 gestures past enough.

17:41.210 --> 17:43.000
(laughs) No, no,
you're gonna want this.

17:43.000 --> 17:45.710
Just don't tell Steven
I gave it to you.

17:49.710 --> 17:52.210
-Is that Bowie?
-Mm-hmm.

17:54.920 --> 17:56.960
Is he eating dog biscuits?

17:56.960 --> 17:59.210
(laughs) There's a lot
more where that came from.

17:59.920 --> 18:02.120
Mom! You're not really leaving
in the morning, are you?

18:02.120 --> 18:04.460
The high seas
are calling.

18:04.460 --> 18:06.620
Plus, I got a cabin upgrade.

18:06.620 --> 18:08.540
And you two?

18:08.540 --> 18:09.380
Everything okay?

18:09.380 --> 18:11.580
-Stop you.
-I love Grandma.

18:11.580 --> 18:12.420
(chuckles)

18:12.420 --> 18:13.420
♪ ♪

18:13.420 --> 18:14.580
Hug?

18:14.580 --> 18:16.290
I'm really gonna
miss those.

18:16.290 --> 18:17.460
Aw...

18:19.880 --> 18:21.080
(sniffles)

18:21.750 --> 18:22.620
Woof.

18:22.620 --> 18:24.420
(laughs)
You're terrible!

18:24.420 --> 18:25.460
(laughs)

18:25.460 --> 18:26.380
Just a little longer.

18:38.170 --> 18:39.960
Jonah:
What are we going to
do when we see Metcalf?

18:39.960 --> 18:41.920
My plan was
not to see him,

18:41.920 --> 18:43.420
for the rest
of the year.

18:44.170 --> 18:45.290
And all of the next.

18:45.290 --> 18:46.750
Or we could pretend
that it never happened.

18:47.500 --> 18:48.920
(whispers)
Pretend what never happened?

18:49.670 --> 18:51.460
That you saw your principal
outside of school?

18:51.460 --> 18:52.580
-Buffy: No.
-Jonah: Not at all.

18:52.580 --> 18:53.580
Really?

18:53.580 --> 18:54.750
Oh. It was weird for me.

18:54.750 --> 18:55.960
-Us, too.
-Extremely weird.

18:55.960 --> 18:57.380
Anything you
wanna ask me?

18:57.380 --> 18:58.710
-Nope.
-I'm, I'm good.

18:58.710 --> 19:00.670
You're not curious why your
principal has a lot of tattoos?

19:02.420 --> 19:04.380
-Of course we're curious.
-Duh.

19:05.790 --> 19:07.710
Each one tells a story.

19:07.710 --> 19:09.460
This was my first.

19:09.460 --> 19:10.670
The story is, uh...

19:11.670 --> 19:13.080
Well, I was 18,
and I wanted a tattoo.

19:13.080 --> 19:14.380
Wow.

19:14.380 --> 19:15.540
I know,
you're thinking I'm cooler

19:15.540 --> 19:17.250
than you thought I was,
aren't you?

19:17.250 --> 19:18.580
No...

19:18.580 --> 19:21.670
I was actually thinking that
now I can't ever get a tattoo

19:21.670 --> 19:23.540
because it's something
teachers do.

19:25.080 --> 19:27.670
Well, yeah, that's... Oh.

19:27.670 --> 19:29.960
(laughing)

19:29.960 --> 19:32.710
♪ ♪

19:44.040 --> 19:46.120
Thanks for
coming with me.

19:46.120 --> 19:47.540
You're doing
the right thing.

19:48.540 --> 19:50.250
That's what
my parents said,

19:50.250 --> 19:52.670
but I think TJ
would disagree.

19:53.540 --> 19:54.790
He's gonna hate me.

19:56.540 --> 19:58.540
You could be saving his life.

19:59.620 --> 20:01.170
Think about it that way.

20:02.250 --> 20:03.250
Okay?

20:04.920 --> 20:05.920
(sighs)

20:10.670 --> 20:11.540
Cyrus.

20:11.540 --> 20:13.120
Looking for me?

20:13.120 --> 20:16.620
Yeah. I needed to talk
to you about something.

20:17.540 --> 20:19.540
I need to talk to you,
too. Come in.

20:23.580 --> 20:24.580
(door shuts)

20:27.000 --> 20:29.210
Cyrus, this is
Officer Wright.

20:29.210 --> 20:30.000
Hello.

20:32.170 --> 20:33.000
Did something happen?

20:33.000 --> 20:35.670
No, nothing happened.
Everyone's okay.

20:35.670 --> 20:37.380
Officer Wright
has some questions.

20:37.380 --> 20:38.580
About?

20:38.580 --> 20:40.500
The gun.

20:40.500 --> 20:41.790
Take a seat.

20:41.790 --> 20:43.120
♪ ♪

20:43.120 --> 20:45.750
That's what I came
in here to tell you about.

20:45.750 --> 20:46.620
The gun.

20:47.620 --> 20:50.540
But, you already know about it?

20:50.540 --> 20:51.960
Yes.

20:52.960 --> 20:55.540
And, now you're questioning me?

20:55.540 --> 20:57.290
You were there, right?

21:00.710 --> 21:02.380
Yeah, I was there.

21:03.880 --> 21:05.920
Am I in trouble?

21:13.580 --> 21:14.750
Andi:
Next on Andi Mack...

21:14.750 --> 21:16.250
Buffy:
I just had one player.

21:16.250 --> 21:18.250
One who knows the game.

21:18.250 --> 21:19.830
Who's played on a team.

21:19.830 --> 21:21.330
Please join the team.

21:21.330 --> 21:22.500
I'm in, slayer.

21:22.500 --> 21:23.500
♪ ♪

21:24.750 --> 21:25.670
Denied!

21:25.670 --> 21:27.960
What's gonna happen
when I'm not holding back?

21:29.120 --> 21:30.210
We're staring.

21:30.210 --> 21:31.620
Andi:
I knew there was somebody.

21:31.620 --> 21:32.880
There's someone
I want you to meet.

21:32.880 --> 21:34.080
I saw you two this morning.

21:34.080 --> 21:35.210
After you walked away,

21:35.210 --> 21:37.170
I tried to introduce
myself to her.

21:37.170 --> 21:38.620
-Hello!
-I called out

21:38.620 --> 21:41.210
several times, but she iced me.
